    • Method Detail

      • hintedAvailability

        public DomainAvailabilityResults hintedAvailability(DomainNameAvailabilityDescriptor descriptor)
                                             throws java.lang.Exception
        Provides fast hinted search results for one or more TLDs or predefined TLD Categories for a supplied domain prefix string. This allows for rapid indicative search results without the overhead of real time checking via each registry. It is strongly recommended that a call is made to the getLiveAvailability function for individual domains before confirming a sale or adding to an application cart. Hinted availability is provided via the use of cached zone file data and an indicator of the cache age is returned as part of the results. Pricing data is returned according to the availability detected and where premium pricing may apply for a given TLD, a hint of the premium status and pricing is returned via cached premium data where available. The returned object contains DomainAvailability objects structured according to the parameters passed.
        Parameters:
        descriptor - descriptor
        Returns:
        Result from function
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Throws server side exceptions of variable types.

      • liveAvailability

        public DomainAvailability liveAvailability(java.lang.String domainName)
                                    throws java.lang.Exception
        Get live domain availability for a single domain name. This actually checks the real time availability with the Registry and returns a single DomainAvailability object with actual availability and confirmed pricing. This method should be called before committing to a sale (usually at the point of adding to a cart).
        Parameters:

      • transferCreate

        public Transaction transferCreate(DomainNameTransferDescriptor transferDescriptor,
                                  java.lang.String bulkOperationProgressKey)
                           throws java.lang.Exception
        Create multiple domains for transfer in. This accepts a transfer descriptor which encodes one or more domain names for transfer in along with proposed contact details. This call should usually be preceded by a call to validateIncomingTransferDomains to confirm auth codes etc. NB: Since the introduction of the 2018 Temporary Specification for GTLD registration data, post transfer contact details need to be supplied upfront when creating / validating incoming transfers as these are no longer readable via WHOIS due to privacy redaction.

        If successful, this method starts the transfer process for the supplied domains by taking payment for the transfer (for Pull Transfer operations) and starting the transfer operation with the Registry. It returns a DomainNameTransaction object detailing the result of the operation. For Pull Transfers: Once a transfer is created it will be added to your account with a status of TRANSFER_IN_AWAITING_RESPONSE until it is either cancelled, accepted, rejected or automatically accepted after 5 days. For Push Transfers: the domain name will be imported and activated within your account.
        Parameters:
        transferDescriptor - transferDescriptor
        bulkOperationProgressKey - bulkOperationProgressKey
        Returns:
        Result from function
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Throws server side exceptions of variable types.

      • transferCancel

        public Transaction transferCancel(java.lang.String[] domainNames)
                           throws java.lang.Exception
        Cancel incoming transfer operations for one or more domain names. Domain transfers can be cancelled while domains have TRANSFER_IN_PENDING_CONFIRMATION or TRANSFER_IN_AWAITING_RESPONSE status (applicable for Pull Transfers only). This operation if successful will cancel the transfer operation and remove the domain name from your account. A DomainNameTransaction object is returned detailing the success or failure for each attempted domain name.
        Parameters:
        domainNames - domainNames
        Returns:
        Result from function
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Throws server side exceptions of variable types.

      • ownerChangeCancel

        public Transaction ownerChangeCancel(java.lang.String[] domainNames)
                              throws java.lang.Exception
        Cancel any pending owner contact changes for the supplied domain names. Pending changes arise when a call to the updateDomainNames method has resulted in a change to key fields for the owner contact of a GTLD. In this case the owner contact will be returned with a status of PENDING_CHANGES. This method will remove the pending data awaiting verification and restore the Owner contact back a status of LIVE with the previous details intact. This returns a DomainNameTransaction object with transaction elements which will be successful if the owner contact is pending changes or will contain an operation error if not successful.
        Parameters:
        domainNames - domainNames
        Returns:
        Result from function
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Throws server side exceptions of variable types.

      • glueRecordsList

        public DomainNameGlueRecord[] glueRecordsList(java.lang.String domainName)
                                       throws java.lang.Exception
        List all previously set glue records for a domain name. Glue records (sometimes called child nameservers) define explicit mappings of subdomains to IP addresses such that the subdomain may be used as a delegated nameserver for other domains or indeed the domain name itself. PLEASE NOTE: This method will only list glue records which have been explicitly set using the setGlueRecords method or via the Netistrar Control Panel. There is no guarantee that this list is the complete list of records defined at the registry if this name has been transferred into Netistrar with existing additional glue records intact. This method returns an array of DomainNameGlueRecord objects currently defined for the domain name
        Parameters:
        domainName - domainName
        Returns:
        Result from function
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Throws server side exceptions of variable types.

      • glueRecordsSet

        public Transaction glueRecordsSet(java.lang.String domainName,
                                  DomainNameGlueRecord[] glueRecords,
                                  java.lang.String bulkOperationProgressKey)
                           throws java.lang.Exception
        Set one or more glue records for a domain name. Glue records (sometimes called child nameservers) define explicit mappings of subdomains to IP addresses such that the subdomain may be used as a delegated nameserver for other domains or indeed the domain name itself. This method accepts a domain name and an array of DomainNameGlueRecord objects which comprise a subdomain prefix and either an ipv4 or ipv6 address or both. It returns a DomainNameTransaction object which encodes the result of the set operation with a transaction element for each glue record passed. If the glue records are in an invalid format or have missing data, a validation error will be returned as part of the element.
        Parameters:
        domainName - domainName
        glueRecords - glueRecords
        bulkOperationProgressKey - bulkOperationProgressKey
        Returns:
        Result from function
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - Throws server side exceptions of variable types.

      • glueRecordsRemove

        public Transaction glueRecordsRemove(java.lang.String domainName,
                                     java.lang.String[] glueRecordSubdomains,
                                     java.lang.String bulkOperationProgressKey)
                              throws java.lang.Exception
        Remove one or more glue records for a domain name. Glue records (sometimes called child nameservers) define explicit mappings of subdomains to IP addresses such that the subdomain may be used as a delegated nameserver for other domains or indeed the domain name itself. This method accepts a domain name and an array of String objects which represent the subdomains to remove as glue records. It returns a DomainNameTransaction object which encodes the result of the remove operation with a transaction element for each glue record passed. Operation errors will be raised if the glue record does not exist or cannot be removed
        Parameters:

        glueRecordSubdomains - glueRecordSubdomains
